Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
unflattenIlm(25.10)                                        unflattenIlm(25.10)

Name
       unflattenIlm - Reverts the ILM back to its original hard macro view

Syntax
       unflattenIlm

       [-help]

       Reverts the ILM back to its original hard macro view.

       You can use this command after the
           flattenIlm
          command.

       Note:  unflattenIlm will take no effect if the design is already in the
       unflattened mode.

       Many physical commands would not work in the flattened mode. They would
       need to be unflattened before performing the operation.

       For example:

       flattenIlm

       report_timing

       unflattenIlm

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the usage of  the  un-
              flattenIlm command.

Example
       The  following command flattens all partitions and their ILM designs to
       the top-level. After reporting timing, the design is reverted  back  to
       the unflattened state with the unflattenIlm command.

       flattenIlm

       report_timing

       unflattenIlm

Related Information
              * flattenIlm

              * report_timing

              * Top-level Timing Closure Methodologies chapter of Innovus User
                Guide.

